 The Opportunity
 Adobe has a world-class research that provides an ideal balance of academic discovery and industry impact: that's what drives our groundbreaking work at Adobe Research. Our research scientists, engineers, artists and designers shape experimental ideas into innovative technologies for Adobe Products.
 During the past 25 years, Adobe PDF has been a defacto digital format for sharing and distributing documents in reliable manners. Adobe Document Cloud is revolutionizing the way the world works with documents and is growing rapidly. As we enter in the new era of AI-powered digital businesses, we continue to strive to invent, design and productize the documents of the future and redefine the user experiences around the documents.
 What you'll Do
 As a senior research scientist in Document Intelligence Lab (DIL), you will provide technical leadership in research, architect and develop machine learning solutions at scale in the following areas:
 semantic document understanding cross modalities (e.g. image, language and structure) knowledge extraction from document collection next-generational experiences in content creation
 You will leverage Adobeâ€™s unique data sources and customer relationships which include not only content (such as images, videos, texts, voicees), but also how the customers interacting with those contents (such as authoring, sharing, viewing, retrieving, and collaborating) in the context of diverse verticals (e.g. financial services, healthcare, government and etc.).
 What you need to succeed
 Demonstrate technical proficiency in state-of-art machine learning and deep learning methods that deal with multi-modality data (e.g. text, image, graph, etc.)
 Initiate, lead and execute research initiatives by collaborating with researchers and engineers in cross-disciplinary and cross-functional environments
 Keep abreast of the latest developments in the fields by continuous learning and proactively championing new ideas and new problem definitions
 Familiar with one or more state-of-art deep learning frameworks, such as Tensorflow, PyTorch, Keras, Caffe, Torch.
 Excellent communication, relationship skills and a strong team player.
 Required Qualifications
 PhD in Computer Science, Electrical Engineering or relevant majors with research specialization in artificial intelligence, machine learning, natural language processing and understanding, multi-modal document analysis.
